The paper deals with the correctness of concurrent data structures, which is a topic in both cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of an interval-based logic suggests a focus on formal methods and program verification, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the verification of linearisability, which is a topic in cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
